ng. 3 cleric and a warrior were never meant to solo uber mobs and you were never meant to own all other classes in the game to that ridiculous extent. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useinclino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seinclino</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/17/02 12:53:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Manaburn and the like</span><hr size=1> Yeah, but remember when you were a newb and you got backstabbed while medding for 90!!!!!! (Well, when you're lvl 8 that's about all you have.) Y'see, Twinked melee classes got to thrash us at early lvls and we didn't stand a chance. I don't care how much you twink a Wizard they can never be Plvld and can never win against a melee; our lvl 8 nuke can by no means outdamgage a twink, especially when that twink is hitting you for 50 dmg 6 times while you cast. I think Wizards earn the right to trash (probably the same people on their mains) everyone at later lvls. I started a Wizard on TZ expecting to burn some peoples arses later on. Though I hear Sunstrike can whipe out a 52 necro in one fell nuke, I don't remember ever getting PKed by a necro until lvl 30. Or maybe I'm still a newb and I just seek vengance. <br><br>Seinclino <br>35 (yeah, I'm a newb) Wizard on TZ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/17/02 6:37:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaburn and the like</span><hr size=1> So your logic is basicly that because some twink beat you up and took your lunch money you should as a lvl 60 wizard be able to own all other players with about as much effort as orc pawns? /boggle.<br><br>Sorry all classes not just casters have to deal with lame pvp twinks.  In fact tanks don't even have the option of shadowstepping.  Gross imbalance is bad kthx?  We would be better off working to limit or eliminate it on pvp servers rather than creating more and worse imbalance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uacillatemzoso.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Acillatem Zoso</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/17/02 9:12:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaburn and the like</span><hr size=1> Lay on Hands = what +5000 max hit points?  Instant cast.  PAL has no ill effect whatsoever and can go about PVPing as if nothing has changed.  Pretty much you hafta kill a PAL twice.<br><br>Harm Touch can = around 1500 - instant cast.  SK has no ill effects whatsoever and can go about PvPing as if nothing happened.<br><br>Disc Backstab = 1500 total damage in 1 round of PvP.  Instant effect time.  No ill effects after using discipline.<br><br>Manaburn = approx 6000 dmg.  6.5 sec cast time.  Leaves the wizard completely helpless, no mana, no nothing.  Wizard better have SoW and better have attacked a lone target.<br><br>With the exception of LoH - all of the above can kill a person.  The difference?  Manaburn takes TIME TO CAST.  <br><br>I am 55.  I wont be getting manaburn for 