list is truely lethal in is nailing a medding caster. Then you may well be dead before you can blink.  My suggestions to avoid this...keep see invis up, med with your back to a wall if possible, watch the area in 3rd person view.<br><br>Other  than that you can't plan on x amount of dmg in that duelist round.  Melee dmg over time is reliable.  Melee dmg on any given round of combat is very unreliable. Only 40% of backstab attempts are double. Only 2/3 land.  This means that less than 20% of backstab attempts will result in 2 attacks that both land. <br><br>Without max str and avatar you wont ever seen a single stab for the theoretical max either I do not have duelist just yet, I'm 57 now, but looking at current stabs I'm guessing without a primal you will see a lot from duelist min 388 to around 800 max as far as stabs. With a lot more tending towards 388 than the high mark.<br><br>This should mean that 4/5 times you should see something like 400-600 dmg if the player is a) smart and b) not poison snared. Unless they move or you get a bit of lag as your triggering the disc round in which case you get 0. Unless of course they have a horse because for god knows what reason you can't bs a mounted person.<br><br>The point is that while there are many counterstrategies to minimize or even avoid the damage done by a duelist rogue there really isn't much to be done about a wizard nuking players for 5000-6000 pvp dmg non crit in 6 seconds from 200 feet away.  You only have to channel once, start casting from far away once, get a good shadowstep and nuke once, nuke me through 2 walls from an entirely different room once, run around a corner and nuke once to gank my items.<br><br>The reason why mannaburn is imbalanced is that it WILL grant the user an easy no skill kill every time its used. No class has the means to defend themselves vs a 5000-6000 point nukes.  Heres a fun idea after you get mannaburn work on exodus the 1/10 of a second gate.  That way you only need 3 hotkeys to pvp...<br><br>mannaburn<br>/loot<br>exodus<br><br>Most high lvl wizards I've talked to agree that mannaburn is way overpowered.  They are nerfing mannaburn in pvp...get over it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhimarutz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HimaruTZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/18/02 11:58:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaburn and the like</span><hr size=1> as for those complaining about it being an &quot;instant kill&quot; my wizard on TZ has found the following:<br><br>Full mana level 60 wizard vs druid around 60- druid's heals can out heal wizzy dmg, not to mention all the free DOT's they get from right clicks.<br><br>Uber melees have 4k+hps. rangers can have resists all above 200, heal almost as well as druids and one beech hits me for 400+ a pop. which means while she is hitting me 4x I am dead.<br><br>As stated earlier melee dmg should be reduced 60% as well as DOT's to 60%.  Originally it was casters were supposed to be weak at lower levels but masters at dmg at higher levels. This doesnt seem to be the case anymore. Nerf the druid spell line and maybe we'll see some improvements. <p>Himaru Gemma <BR>Upon the face of Innoruuk a smirk was made as the breath entered Himaru's lungs. "He will destroy all that is living, and that is good" Innoruuk said.<img src="http://community.redclouds.com/okhoney/jokes/afterhourstubbies.JPG" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br